9. Troubleshooting and step-by-step commands
- If tests fail locally:
  1) Run npm run test:unit to get coverage-enabled detailed failures.
  2) Inspect tests/unit/main.test.js and src/lib/main.js for mismatches.
  3) Run vitest directly with verbose flags, if needed.
- If node version mismatch occurs: confirm node --version >= 24.0.0 or use nvm to switch.
- If agentic workflows behave unexpectedly: check agentic-lib.toml schedule and model keys, and verify workflow files in .github/agentic-lib are up to date with upstream.

